platformType.name: platformType
platformType.description: The platform type. Currently, only one platform is defined: Starfire. There is no plan to backport to CS6400 yet.

platformName.name: platformName
platformName.description: The name assigned to a physical machine.

platformAmbientTemp.name: platformAmbientTemp
platformAmbientTemp.description: The current ambient temperature of the platform. The temperature will be in Celsius.

platformInterconnectClockFreq.name: platformInterconnectClockFreq
platformInterconnectClockFreq.description: This member is the current interconnect frequency of the platform. The unit is in Hz.

platformProcClockFreq.name: platformProcClockFreq
platformProcClockFreq.description: This member is the current processor clock frequency of the platform. The unit is in Hz.

platformJtagClockFreq.name: platformJtagClockFreq
platformJtagClockFreq.description: This member is the current JTAG clock frequency of the platform. The unit is in Hz. Note: this member is only measurable in the rev-3 control board. If this unit is not available (rev-1 or rev-2 control board), the returning value is set to 0 Hz.

platformTargetInterconnectClockFreq.name: platformTargetInterconnectClockFreq
platformTargetInterconnectClockFreq.description: This member is the targeted interconnect clock frequency. The unit is in Hz and the valid range is between 40,000,000 Hz and 120,000,000 Hz. The platformTargetInterconnectClockFreq, platformTargetProcClockMultiple and platformTargetJtagClockFreq must be established prior to system operation. They are used as the guideline to set up the interconnect, processor and JTAG clock frequency of the platform. These value are maintained in SSP persistent store.

platformTargetProcClockMultiple.name: platformTargetProcClockMultiple
platformTargetProcClockMultiple.description: This member is the targeted processor clock frequency expressed in terms of a specific factor of the system clock. Possible options are factor of 2 or 3. See platformTargetInterconnectClockFreq for more detail. A possible Blackbird processor would use the 3:2 ratio.

platformTargetJtagClockFreq.name: platformTargetJtagClockFreq
platformTargetJtagClockFreq.description: This member is the targeted JTAG clock frequency. The unit is in Hz. See platformTargetSystemClockFreq for more detail.

platformMasterConBrd.name: platformMasterConBrd
platformMasterConBrd.description: This member is the master control board number.

platformSysClkConBrd.name: platformSysClkConBrd
platformSysClkConBrd.description: This member is the control board providing system clock to the platform.

confNumDomain.name: confNumDomain
confNumDomain.description: The number of domain in the platform. Domains are created with command, domain_create. Domains are removed with command, domain_remove.

confNumSysBrd.name: confNumSysBrd
confNumSysBrd.description: The number of system board in the platform. The max # system board in a Starfire system is 16.

confNumProc.name: confNumProc
confNumProc.description: The number of processor in a system board. The max # processors in a Starfire system is 64.

confNumConBrd.name: confNumConBrd
confNumConBrd.description: The number of control board in the system. The max # control board in a Starfire system is 2.

confNumCenterplane.name: confNumCenterplane
confNumCenterplane.description: The number of centerplane in the system. The max # centerplane half board in a Starfire system is 2.

confNumSuppBrd.name: confNumSuppBrd
confNumSuppBrd.description: The number of centerplane support board in the system. The max # of centerplane support board in a Starfire system is 2.

confNumIoCab.name: confNumIoCab
confNumIoCab.description: The number of IO cabinet connected to the system. The max # of IO cabinets that can be connected to a Starfire system is 3.

confNumFanTray.name: confNumFanTray
confNumFanTray.description: The number of fan tray in the system. The max # of fan trays that can be installed in a Starfire system is 16.

confNumBulkPower.name: confNumBulkPower
confNumBulkPower.description: The number of bulk power supply in the system. The max # of bulk power supply in a Starfire system is 8.

confNumSysBrdPower.name: confNumSysBrdPower
confNumSysBrdPower.description: The number of system board power supply in the system. The max # of system board power supply for a Starfire system is 16. In Starfire, system board power supply is not a separate entity. It is integrated in a system board.

confSysBrdList.name: confSysBrdList
confSysBrdList.description: A string identifying the system boards that are present in the system. The format of the string is: xx-xx-.. where xx is the system board number and the delimiter is a dash.

confProcList.name: confProcList
confProcList.description: A string identifying the processors that are present in the system. The format of the string is: bb.pp-bb.pp-... where bb is the system board number and pp is the processor number within a system board, the delimiter is a dash.

confConBrdList.name: confConBrdList
confConBrdList.description: A string identifying the control boards that are present in the system. The format of the string is: xx-xx-.. where xx is the control board number and dash is the delimiter.

confCenterplaneList.name: confCenterplaneList
confCenterplaneList.description: A string identifying the centerplanes that are present in the system. The format of the string is: xx-xx-.. where xx is the centerplane number and dash is the delimiter.

confSuppBrdList.name: confSuppBrdList
confSuppBrdList.description: A string identifying the centerplane support boards that are present in the system. The format of the string is: xx-xx-... where xx is the centerplane support board number and dash is the delimiter.

confIoCabList.name: confIoCabList
confIoCabList.description: A string identifying the IO cabinets that are connected to the system. The format of the string is: xx-xx-... where xx is the I/O cabinet number and dash is the delimiter.

confFanTrayList.name: confFanTrayList
confFanTrayList.description: A string identifying the fan trays that are present in the system. the format of the string is: xx-xx-... where xx is the fan tray number and dash is the delimiter.

confBulkPowerList.name: confBulkPowerList
confBulkPowerList.description: A string identifying the bulk power supplies that are present in the system. The format of the string is: x-x where x is the bulk power supply number and dash is the delimiter. Bulk power supplies are numbered 0 to 7.

confSysBrdPowerList.name: confSysBrdPowerList
confSysBrdPowerList.description: A string identifying the system board power supplies that are present in the system. The format of the string: xx-xx-... where xx is the system board power supply number and dash is the delimiter.

confMaxProcPerSysBrd.name: confMaxProcPerSysBrd
confMaxProcPerSysBrd.description: The maximum number of processor in a system board. There is a max of 4 processors in a Starfire system board.

confMaxFanPerTray.name: confMaxFanPerTray
confMaxFanPerTray.description: The maximum number of fan in a fan tray. There is a max of 2 fan in a Starfire fan tray.

confMaxLEDPerFanTray.name: confMaxLEDPerFanTray
confMaxLEDPerFanTray.description: The maximum number of LED in a fan tray. There is a max of 2 LEDs in a Starfire fan tray.

confMaxLEDPerBulkPower.name: confMaxLEDPerBulkPower
confMaxLEDPerBulkPower.description: The maximum number of LED in a bulk power supply. There is a max of 2 LEDs in a Starfire bulk power supply.

confMaxLEDPerSysBrd.name: confMaxLEDPerSysBrd
confMaxLEDPerSysBrd.description: The maximum number of LED in a system board.

confMemAddrMap.name: confMemAddrMap
confMemAddrMap.description: Starfire supports Shared Memory Domains. This requires the memory boards in the machine to have unique address. Because of this global requirement, Starfire hpost assigns the memory addresses, as well as for attaching boards. DR detach operation also assigns memory addresses. The method used to ensure unique addresses is to assign addresses based on slot number. To allow for 2 way inter-board interleaving, these addresses are slot number*8G. The map is a 16-byte array representing the 16 slots. The lower 7 bits of each byte represents the unique address assign to that slot. The high bit is significant on a write-operation only, when set the corresponding slot of the map will be changed with the address represented by the lower 7 bits. On a read operation the returning data represents the current memory map and the high bit of each byte is always 0. On a write operation the byte with the high bit set will be modified. The SNMP agent will perform a consistency check before committing a write operation. Consistency check simply makes sure no two slots will contain the same address if the write is performed. If consistency check fails, the write operation will return an error.

domainTable.name: domainTable
domainTable.description: The domain table. The number of entries in the table is given by conf.confNumDomain.

domainIndex.name: domainIndex
domainIndex.description: A number assigned to a domain.

domainNumSysBrd.name: domainNumSysBrd
domainNumSysBrd.description: The number of system board assigned to this domain.

domainSysBrdList.name: domainSysBrdList
domainSysBrdList.description: A list of system board entries belonging to this domain. The number of boards is given by domainNumSysBrd. The format of the string is: xx-xx where xx is the system board number and dash is the delimiter.

domainOSVersion.name: domainOSVersion
domainOSVersion.description: The OS version for this domain.

domainProcList.name: domainProcList
domainProcList.description: A list of processors belonging to this domain. The format of the string is in: ss.bb-ss.bb-... where ss is the system board number, bb is the processor number within a system board, and dash is the delimiter.

domainBootProc.name: domainBootProc
domainBootProc.description: The boot processor number of this domain. If the value is -1, that means the domain is not configured/booted.

domainInterruptVector.name: domainInterruptVector
domainInterruptVector.description: Interrupts to the host processor via JTAG requires 2 pieces of information: the UPA ID of the target CPU and the interrupt number assigned to the bootbus interrupt by the host. The target UPA ID identifies the particular bootbus and the proc ID (0 or 1) to be written into the bootbus interrupt register. The interrupt number is the value to be written into word 0 of the mondo vector of the target CPU. This number is computed by the host kernel. This object is a 13 bit value and is treated as an integer (32 bit) for easy manipulation.

domainSysBrdConfig.name: domainSysBrdConfig
domainSysBrdConfig.description: A list of configured system board entries belonging to this domain. The format of the string is: xx-xx where xx is the system board number and dash is the delimiter.

domainProcConfig.name: domainProcConfig
domainProcConfig.description: POST scans both blacklist and redlist files to determine which components should not be used to configure a domain. The content of the blacklist and redlist files along with the final result of a POST run is kept in a data structure, P2OBP, in the boot processor's BBSRAM. The SNMP agent is responsible to retrieve the data structure and extracts the necessary information to produce the result. domainProcConfig describes the processors configuration. Its format is a DisplayString (character string) in the format of xx.yyS-xx.yyS-... where xx is a system board number [0..15], yy is a processor number within a system board [0..3], S is a single character status code, and (dash) '-' is for delimiting multiple components. Valid status code include: F - Tested and Failed M - Missing R - Redlisted B - Blacklisted c - Crunched U - Good but not configured G - Good A - Architecturally missing

domainABusConfig.name: domainABusConfig
domainABusConfig.description: domainAbusConfig describes the address bus configuration. Its format is a DisplayString in the format of xxS-xxS-... where xx is an address bus [0..3] and S is a status code (see domainProcConfig).

domainDBusConfig.name: domainDBusConfig
domainDBusConfig.description: domainDbusConfig describes the data bus configuration. Its format is a DisplayString in the format of xxS-xxS where xx is a data bus [0..1] and S is a status code (see domainProcConfig).

sysBrdGenTable.name: sysBrdGenTable
sysBrdGenTable.description: System board table. The number host of entries in the table is represented by Conf.ConfNumSysBrd.

sysBrdGenNum.name: sysBrdGenNum
sysBrdGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to a system board. Index begins with 1.

sysBrdGenPower.name: sysBrdGenPower
sysBrdGenPower.description: Power status of the system board. To control power to a system board, modify the sysBrdGenPowerControl.

sysBrdGenNumProc.name: sysBrdGenNumProc
sysBrdGenNumProc.description: Number of processor that are present in this system board.

sysBrdGenProcList.name: sysBrdGenProcList
sysBrdGenProcList.description: A string containing the processors list that are present in this system board. The format of the string is: xx-xx where xx is the processor number within a system board, and dash is the delimiter.

sysBrdGenReset.name: sysBrdGenReset
sysBrdGenReset.description: This member resets the system board.

sysBrdGenPowerControl.name: sysBrdGenPowerControl
sysBrdGenPowerControl.description: On reading it returns the power status of this system board power supply. On writing, it turns on/off this system board power supply.

procStateGenNum.name: procStateGenNum
procStateGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to each CPU.

procStateGenHeartbeat.name: procStateGenHeartbeat
procStateGenHeartbeat.description: A counter being updated by the kernel. This serves an as indicator that the kernel is alive and well.

procStateGenPgmSignature.name: procStateGenPgmSignature
procStateGenPgmSignature.description: This value represents the current program running on a processor. Only 4 programs are identified: POST, Download_helper, OBP, and the kernel.

procStateGenPgmState.name: procStateGenPgmState
procStateGenPgmState.description: This value represents the current state of the program running on a processor. #define SIGBST_NONE 0 /* no state */ #define SIGBST_RUN 1 /* running */ #define SIGBST_EXIT 2 /* finished */ #define SIGBST_PRERUN 3 /* pre-exec */ #define SIGBST_ARBSTOP 4 /* transient arbstop state */ #define SIGBST_RESET 5 /* reset */ #define SIGBST_POWEROFF 6 /* no power */ #define SIGBST_DETACHED 7 /* spinning in OBP after DR DETACH */ #define SIGBST_CALLBACK 8 /* kernel calling back into OBP */ #define SIGBST_WATCHDOG 9 /* OBP running after watchdog */ #define SIGBST_WATCHDOG_SYNC 10 /* OBP sync after watchdog reset */ #define SIGBST_OFFLINE 11 /* cpu offline */ #define SIGBST_BOOTING 12 /* booting */ #define SIGBST_UNKNOWN 13 /* unknown */ #define SIGBST_XIR 14 /* OBP running after XIR */ #define SIGBST_XIR_SYNC 15 /* OBP trying sync in XIR */ #define SIGBST_SIR 16 /* OBP running after SIR */ #define SIGBST_SIR_SYNC 17 /* OBP trying sync in SIR */ #define SIGBST_REDMODE 18 /* OBP running after REDMODE */ #define SIGBST_REDMODE_SYNC 19 /* OBP trying sync in REDMODE */ #define SIGBST_QUIESCED 20 /* system quiesced */ #define SIGBST_QUIESCE_INPROGRESS 21 /* system quiesce in-progress */ #define SIGBST_RESUME_INPROGRESS 22 /* system resume in-progress */

procStateGenPgmSubState.name: procStateGenPgmSubState
procStateGenPgmSubState.description: This value represents a finer detail of the current state of the program running on a processor. #define EXIT_NULL 0 #define EXIT_HALT 1 #define EXIT_ENVIRON 2 #define EXIT_REBOOT 3 #define EXIT_PANIC1 4 #define EXIT_PANIC2 5 #define EXIT_HUNG 6 #define EXIT_WATCH 7 #define EXIT_PANIC_REBOOT 8 #define EXIT_WATCHDOG_REBOOT 9 #define EXIT_SOFT_INIT_RESET 10 /* SIR */ #define EXIT_EXTERN_INIT_RESET 11 /* XIR */ #define EXIT_REDMODE_REBOOT 12 /* REDMODE */ #define EXIT_OBP_RESET 13 /* OBP RESET */

procCommGenTable.name: procCommGenTable
procCommGenTable.description: A table of processor communication entries.

procCommGenIndex.name: procCommGenIndex
procCommGenIndex.description: A unique number assigned to each CPU.

procCommGenNum.name: procCommGenNum
procCommGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to each CPU.

procCommGenSspMboxLen.name: procCommGenSspMboxLen
procCommGenSspMboxLen.description: The length of SSP-to-Host mailbox. This mailbox is used to instruct the host to perform a specific command.

procCommGenSspMboxData.name: procCommGenSspMboxData
procCommGenSspMboxData.description: The data in the SSP-to-Host mailbox.

procCommGenHostMboxData.name: procCommGenHostMboxData
procCommGenHostMboxData.description: The data in the Host-to-SSP mailbox. This mailbox serves for communication between OBP running on the host and obp_helper running on the SSP.

procCommGenObpMboxCmd.name: procCommGenObpMboxCmd
procCommGenObpMboxCmd.description: The command of Obp-to-SSP mailbox. #define SSPC_MULTIPROC 0x0b0b0001 /* Request to release slave CPUs */ #define SSPC_GETTOD 0x0b0b0002 /* Get Unix time of day from SSP */ #define SSPC_GETEEPROM 0x0b0b0003 /* Get EEPROM image from SSP */ #define SSPC_PUTEEPROM 0x0b0b0004 /* Put EEPROM image to SSP */ #define SSPC_UPDREBOOT 0x0b0b0005 /* Invalidate Reboot-info in eeprom */ #define SSPC_MOVECPU0 0x0b0b0006 /* Move Cpu0 Command */ #define SSPC_GETAPDATABASELOC 0x0b0b0007 /* Get AP database location */ #define SSPC_SAVEBOOTPATH 0x0b0b0008 /* Store boot path info */

procCommGenObpMboxData.name: procCommGenObpMboxData
procCommGenObpMboxData.description: The data in the Obp-to-SSP mailbox.

cbGenTable.name: cbGenTable
cbGenTable.description: A table of general control board entries.

cbGenEntry.name: cbGenEntry
cbGenEntry.description: A general control board table entry.

cbGenNum.name: cbGenNum
cbGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to a control board.

cbGenPower.name: cbGenPower
cbGenPower.description: Power status of the control board.

cbGenPowerControl.name: cbGenPowerControl
cbGenPowerControl.description: On writing, it turns off this control board power supply. By default, control board is powered on automatically upon insertion to the cabinet or when house keeping power is applied. On reading, it always returns off.

ioCabGenTable.name: ioCabGenTable
ioCabGenTable.description: A table of general IO cabinet entries.

ioCabGenEntry.name: ioCabGenEntry
ioCabGenEntry.description: A general I/O cabinet table entry.

ioCabGenNum.name: ioCabGenNum
ioCabGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to an I/O Cabinet.

ioCabGenPower.name: ioCabGenPower
ioCabGenPower.description: A value identifying the current power state of an IO cabinet and also for powering on and off the I/O cabinet.

fanTrayGenTable.name: fanTrayGenTable
fanTrayGenTable.description: A table of fan tray entries.

fanTrayGenNum.name: fanTrayGenNum
fanTrayGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to a fan tray.

fanTrayGenPower.name: fanTrayGenPower
fanTrayGenPower.description: On reading this object, it returns the power status of this fan tray. On writing it turns on/off the fan tray power.

fanGenTable.name: fanGenTable
fanGenTable.description: A table of fan entries. Each fan tray has certain number of fans. The number is represented by ConfMaxFanPerTray.

fanGenEntry.name: fanGenEntry
fanGenEntry.description: A fan tray entry containing information about a fan tray. Each fan entry is uniquely identified by 2 fields: fan tray number and fan number.

fanGenTraySlotNum.name: fanGenTraySlotNum
fanGenTraySlotNum.description: A unique number assigned to a fan tray slot.

fanGenNum.name: fanGenNum
fanGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to a fan inside this tray.

fanGenStatus.name: fanGenStatus
fanGenStatus.description: On reading it returns the power status of this fan. On writing it allows an application to turn on/off this fan.

fanGenSpeed.name: fanGenSpeed
fanGenSpeed.description: On reading it returns the speed of this fan inside a fan tray. On writing, it allows one to change the speed of this fan. Nominal is the medium speed the fan will support, and fast is the highest fastest speed the fan will support.

fanGenPowerControl.name: fanGenPowerControl
fanGenPowerControl.description: The MIB object that is used to either power on or off this fan. The power status of this fan should be read from the fanGenStatus MIB object. On writing, the fan is either turned on or off.

suppBrdGenTable.name: suppBrdGenTable
suppBrdGenTable.description: A table of support board entries.

suppBrdGenIndex.name: suppBrdGenIndex
suppBrdGenIndex.description: A unique number assigned to this support board.

suppBrdGenNum.name: suppBrdGenNum
suppBrdGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to this support board.

suppBrdGenPower.name: suppBrdGenPower
suppBrdGenPower.description: Power status of the support board.

suppBrdGenPowerControl.name: suppBrdGenPowerControl
suppBrdGenPowerControl.description: On reading it returns the power status of this support board power suuply. On writing, it turns on/off this support board power supply.

bulkPowerGenTable.name: bulkPowerGenTable
bulkPowerGenTable.description: A table of bulk power supply entries.

bulkPowerGenEntry.name: bulkPowerGenEntry
bulkPowerGenEntry.description: A bulk power supply table entry.

bulkPowerGenNum.name: bulkPowerGenNum
bulkPowerGenNum.description: A unique number assigned to this bulk power supply.

bulkPowerGenControl.name: bulkPowerGenControl
bulkPowerGenControl.description: The MIB object that is used to power off this bulk power supply. On writing, it powers off this bulk power supply.

bulkPowerGenStatus.name: bulkPowerGenStatus
bulkPowerGenStatus.description: Power status of the bulk power supply. A status of ok implies the unit is on and supplying enough voltage/current. A status of fail implies the unit is on but not supplying enough voltage/current or the unit is off.

sysBrdStarfireTable.name: sysBrdStarfireTable
sysBrdStarfireTable.description: System board table. The number host of entries in the table is represented by Conf.ConfNumSysBrd.

sysBrdStarfireNum.name: sysBrdStarfireNum
sysBrdStarfireNum.description: A unique number assigned to a system board.

sysBrdStarfireCIC0Temp.name: sysBrdStarfireCIC0Temp
sysBrdStarfireCIC0Temp.description: The temperature of the CIC0 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireCIC1Temp.name: sysBrdStarfireCIC1Temp
sysBrdStarfireCIC1Temp.description: The temperature of the CIC1 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireMCTemp.name: sysBrdStarfireMCTemp
sysBrdStarfireMCTemp.description: The temperature of the MC ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireXDB2Temp.name: sysBrdStarfireXDB2Temp
sysBrdStarfireXDB2Temp.description: The temperature of the XDB2 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireXDB3Temp.name: sysBrdStarfireXDB3Temp
sysBrdStarfireXDB3Temp.description: The temperature of the XDB3 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfirePROC0Temp.name: sysBrdStarfirePROC0Temp
sysBrdStarfirePROC0Temp.description: The temperature of the PROC0 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfirePROC1Temp.name: sysBrdStarfirePROC1Temp
sysBrdStarfirePROC1Temp.description: The temperature of the PROC1 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfirePROC2Temp.name: sysBrdStarfirePROC2Temp
sysBrdStarfirePROC2Temp.description: The temperature of the PROC2 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfirePROC3Temp.name: sysBrdStarfirePROC3Temp
sysBrdStarfirePROC3Temp.description: The temperature of the PROC3 ASIC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCTemp.name: sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCTemp
sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCTemp.description: The temperature of the PS2 3.3V DC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireVDCCoreTemp.name: sysBrdStarfireVDCCoreTemp
sysBrdStarfireVDCCoreTemp.description: The temperature of the PS3 VDD Core on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfire5VDCTemp.name: sysBrdStarfire5VDCTemp
sysBrdStarfire5VDCTemp.description: The temperature of the PS5 5V DC on this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfire3p3VDC.name: sysBrdStarfire3p3VDC
sysBrdStarfire3p3VDC.description: The VDD voltage reading of this Starfire system board, which is equivalent to 3.3VDC.

sysBrdStarfire5VDCHK.name: sysBrdStarfire5VDCHK
sysBrdStarfire5VDCHK.description: The 5V DC housekeeping voltage reading of this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfire5VDC.name: sysBrdStarfire5VDC
sysBrdStarfire5VDC.description: The 5V DC voltage reading of this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfireVDCCore.name: sysBrdStarfireVDCCore
sysBrdStarfireVDCCore.description: The VDD Core voltage reading of this Starfire system board.

sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCHK.name: sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCHK
sysBrdStarfire3p3VDCHK.description: The 3.3V DC voltage reading of this Starfire system board.

cbStarfireTable.name: cbStarfireTable
cbStarfireTable.description: A table of control board entries.

cbStarfireNum.name: cbStarfireNum
cbStarfireNum.description: A unique number assigned to a control board.

cbStarfireHostName.name: cbStarfireHostName
cbStarfireHostName.description: Host name assigned to this control board.

cbStarfireSen0Temp.name: cbStarfireSen0Temp
cbStarfireSen0Temp.description: The temperature of the 1st temperature sensor.

cbStarfireSen1Temp.name: cbStarfireSen1Temp
cbStarfireSen1Temp.description: The temperature of the 2nd temperature sensor.

cbStarfireSen2Temp.name: cbStarfireSen2Temp
cbStarfireSen2Temp.description: The temperature of the 3rd temperature sensor.

cbStarfire5VDCHK.name: cbStarfire5VDCHK
cbStarfire5VDCHK.description: The voltage reading of housekeeping 5V DC.

cbStarfire3p3VDCHK.name: cbStarfire3p3VDCHK
cbStarfire3p3VDCHK.description: The voltage reading of housekeeping 3.3V DC.

centerplaneStarfireNum.name: centerplaneStarfireNum
centerplaneStarfireNum.description: A unique number assigned to this centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp0.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp0
centerplaneStarfireTemp0.description: The 1st temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp1.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp1
centerplaneStarfireTemp1.description: The 2nd temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp2.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp2
centerplaneStarfireTemp2.description: The 3rd temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp3.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp3
centerplaneStarfireTemp3.description: The 4th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp4.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp4
centerplaneStarfireTemp4.description: The 5th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp5.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp5
centerplaneStarfireTemp5.description: The 6th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp6.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp6
centerplaneStarfireTemp6.description: The 7th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp7.name: centerplaneStarfireTemp7
centerplaneStarfireTemp7.description: The 8th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

centerplaneStarfireTemp9.description: The 10th temp point of this Starfire centerplane.

suppBrdStarfireTable.description: A table of support board entries.

suppBrdStarfireNum.name: suppBrdStarfireNum
suppBrdStarfireNum.description: A unique number assigned to this support board.

suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC1Temp.description: The PS1 temp point of this Starfire support board.

suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC2Temp.name: suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC2Temp
suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC2Temp.description: The PS2 temp point of this Starfire support board.

suppBrdStarfire3p3VDCHK.description: The 3.3V DC housekeeping voltage in this Starfire support board.

suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC.name: suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC
suppBrdStarfire3p3VDC.description: The CP 3.3V DC housekeeping voltage in this Starfire support board.

sspPlatformAppEddControl.name: sspPlatformAppEddControl
sspPlatformAppEddControl.description: The object identifies the action intended for the EDD. Changing this object will cause the agent to send a eddControl trap. Reading this object returns the last action requested for the EDD. The SNMP agent does not maintain persistent information for this object. It will be initialized to unknown value.

sspPlatformAppEddState.name: sspPlatformAppEddState

domainChange.name: domainChange
domainChange.description: This trap indicates the domain table has changed. The first two variables (platformName and confNumDomain) will always have an instance value of 0. The remaining variables (domainName, domainNumSysBrd, domainSysBrdList, domainOSVersion, platformType, platformName ) will have an instance value of 0 to confNumDomain - 1. An instance of these remaining variables describe a domain. All variables for this trap are mandatory.

eddState.name: eddState
